# Project Structure Rules

Follow the established project structure when creating or modifying files.

## Directory Organization

```
mistral-b-grc/
├── src/                      # Python source code only
│   └── fintuning/           # Fine-tuning modules
├── configs/                  # YAML configuration files
├── docs/                     # ALL documentation (*.md)
├── notebooks/                # Jupyter notebooks
├── training_dataset/         # JSONL training data
├── data/                     # Data storage
│   ├── raw/                 # Raw datasets
│   ├── processed/           # Processed datasets
│   └── models/              # Trained models
├── scripts/                  # Setup and utility scripts
├── tests/                    # Test files (modify only when requested)
├── .cursor/                  # Cursor IDE configuration
│   └── rules/               # Rule files (.mdc)
└── pyproject.toml           # Project config and dependencies
```

## File Placement Rules

| File Type | Location |
|-----------|----------|
| Python source code | `src/` |
| Configuration files (YAML) | `configs/` |
| Documentation (Markdown) | `docs/` (except root README.md) |
| Jupyter notebooks | `notebooks/` |
| Training data (JSONL) | `training_dataset/` |
| Test files | `tests/` |
| Setup scripts | `scripts/` |

## Configuration Files
- Use YAML format (`.yml` or `.yaml`)
- Place in `configs/` directory
- Name descriptively (e.g., `qlora.yml`, `training.yml`)

## When Creating New Files
1. Determine the correct directory based on file type
2. Follow existing naming conventions
3. Update relevant documentation if needed (only when explicitly requested)
